{% block user %}
Map the column headers from this CSV file to canonical CAFM field names.

File: {{ source_filename }}

Raw headers:
{{ headers | join(', ') }}

{% if sample_rows %}
Sample rows ({{ sample_rows | length }} rows shown):
{% for row in sample_rows[:5] %}{{ row }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

Canonical CAFM field registry:
  Assets:        asset_code, asset_name, category, location_code, make, model, serial
  Work Orders:   wo_code, wo_priority, wo_status, wo_type, maintenance_type
  Scheduled PM:  sm_code, trigger_type, schedule_interval, sm_priority
  Parts:         part_code, stock_on_hand, minimum_allowed_stock, supplier, bom_group_name
  Users:         user_full_name, user_title, user_name, reports_to
  Inspections:   inspector_name, inspection_date, inspection_location, finding_type, risk_level

Known client file → entity type hints:
  assets.csv → assets
  parts.csv → spare_parts (part_code, stock_on_hand, minimum_allowed_stock)
  work_orders.csv → work_orders
  scheduled_pm.csv → maintenance_plans (sm_code, trigger_type)
  task_groups.csv → work_order_tasks
  users.csv → users

Return a JSON object:
{
  "mapping": {
    "raw_header": "canonical_field_name"
  },
  "unmatched": ["headers with no canonical match"],
  "entity_type": "assets | spare_parts | work_orders | maintenance_plans | users | unknown",
  "confidence_per_column": {
    "raw_header": 0.95
  },
  "overall_confidence": 0.90
}

Rules:
- Map every raw header to the single best canonical field.
- Confidence scoring: 1.0 exact, 0.9 clear synonym, 0.7 probable, < 0.6 = add to unmatched.
- overall_confidence: weighted average of confidence scores across all columns.
- unmatched: include any header with confidence < 0.6 — these go to raw_metadata JSONB.
- Use the sample rows to resolve ambiguous headers (e.g. "Code" → asset_code if values look like MOB-AHU-001).
- entity_type: the CAFM entity that best describes ALL the data (one entity type per file).
{% endblock %}
